==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hysteria
<hw>Hys*te"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.: cf. F.
<ets>hyst⟦eacute⟧rie</ets>. See <er>Hysteric</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A nervous affection, occurring almost exclusively
in women, in which the emotional and reflex excitability is exaggerated,
and the will power correspondingly diminished, so that the patient loses
control over the emotions, becomes the victim of imaginary sensations,
and often falls into paroxism or fits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The chief symptoms are convulsive, tossing movements of
the limbs and head, uncontrollable crying and laughing, and a choking
sensation as if a ball were lodged in the throat. The affection presents
the most varied symptoms, often simulating those of the gravest
diseases, but generally curable by mental treatment alone.</note></p>

<p><ent>Hysterical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hysteric</ent>⟦br⟧
